page_title: Creative machines, Using Washing Machine Motors and other cheap bits
aduiance:
Public group  · 55 membersDuring the industrial revolution many machines were set up originally using manual or animal labor. Then water and steam were added to the list. The development path is clear. First set up a process manually then mechanize it.
This is the stage I was with with my ancient lathe. 
I was fortunate to have a good education in electronics so I developed the controller. With a little help from my friendly washing machine breaker (Barrow domestic appliances) the lathe now works.
This site is for the many people out there who dare to think "outside the box" to" boldly go where few have gone before" and make somethink to carry out a task.
My message to big industries with their armies of accountants is clear. Find some way of valuing the skills of your people and to trade unions learn to be flexible in a changing world before the country is dragged to its knees. 
Jimmy Ried kept the Clyde shipyard open for 2 years. this is a landmark achievment.3 posts a week|Public group  · 55 members
